here I am combining the ldat loom files I generated with velocyto in python.

# Read each loom file into a list
ldat_list = lapply(loom_files, ReadVelocity)


# Combine the loom data into a single list of matrices
combine_loom = function(ldat_list) {
  spliced_matrices = lapply(ldat_list, function(ldat) as.matrix(ldat$spliced))
  unspliced_matrices = lapply(ldat_list, function(ldat) as.matrix(ldat$unspliced))
  
  combined_spliced = do.call(cbind, spliced_matrices)
  combined_unspliced = do.call(cbind, unspliced_matrices)
  
  list(spliced = combined_spliced, unspliced = combined_unspliced)
}


###processing####
combined_ldat = combine_loom(ldat_list)

Here I am downsampling the neutrophils to save compute time but also preserving the general shape of the data

neuts.small = subset(neuts, downsample = 1000)
rm(neuts)
common_cells = intersect(colnames(emat), colnames(neuts.small@assays$SCT@counts))
emat = emat[, common_cells]
nmat = nmat[, common_cells]

This chunk is for calculating relative velocities and projecting on umap embeddings. This UMAP is what eventually make it into figure 2A
